Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Did I say it right?//I’m <NPCName>Wakuu</>. It’s a pleasure to meet you. Dad told me about you. He’s the one who brought you here on the chicken boat.//<portrait=happy>Yep, the one with the hat.
Did I hear a Pokyo accent?//<portrait=normal>Oh, you are? Where in Pokyo are you from?
Which hill?
Oh, right, the thingy… Yes, of course.
I see… The busy part. The place with lots of cars and tall buildings, I bet.
Try and stay dry, okay?
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the rain.
Try and stay dry, okay?//It’s stormy today.
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.
I’d love to chat, but I don’t want to make you stand out here in the storm.
Nice weather, huh?
I’m glad for this rain. The plants needed it.
Can you believe Spring’s almost over? It really flew by, didn’t it?
It’s been great spending so much time outdoors. I like Summer too, but Spring’s my favorite season.
Mmm, Fall. I just love the way the air smells this time of year.
It’s crisp and kind of…spicy? I don’t know what it is, but it makes me want to spend all day hiking in the woods.
I try to visit my dad every weekend.//It might sound old-fashioned, but I kind of see it as my duty to check in on him and make sure he has what he needs.
He’s getting older, you know.
<PlayerName>$player</>! I’ll be at the Tavern tonight, playing pool with the gang. You should join us!
Spring, finally! I’ve been itching to spend some nice days outdoors.
What do you think of this weather, huh? Another gorgeous Spring day.
I know they’re good for me, but…green smoothies? Ugh. Can’t stand them.
It’s always amazed me that when we look at the stars, we’re seeing light from thousands of years ago.
Some of the stars we see don’t even exist anymore! They burned out long ago. It just took this long for the light to reach us.
Can’t talk right now. I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!
How’s it going at your farm, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Sure, I’d love to! Thanks for the invite.

Special.SourceString: Great! You should stop by and see what I’m growing.

Text.SourceString: Nah, I’m sure you have it under control. You seem like someone who stays on top of things.

Special.SourceString: Okay, I guess. Sometimes I think I’m in over my head.

Text.SourceString: Walking to the Coffee Corner is how I make sure I get my walking in.//<portrait=normal>If I didn’t, I’d be in my office all the time… That would <Italic>not</> be good.
I don’t really go to the hot spring, even though I live right next to it.
Sometimes I’m too lazy to go grocery shopping.//I just eat whatever we have or go to the Tavern and put leftovers in the fridge.
I was gardening with my dad yesterday, and his plants are looking pretty unhappy. Maybe you can go over there and give him some pointers.
Maybe we overwatered them.//I don’t know.
I’m expecting more rain in Summer.//Let’s hope my expectations are met.
The lighthouse, where my dad lives, gets really stuffy when it’s this humid.//I try to keep the door open during the day to let the air in… Not sure if it helps or not.
I need to make sure Dad’s heater works properly this Winter.//<portrait=concerned>I’ll order him some extra blankets too, maybe.
The neighbors usually have this big dinner party at the end of Winter.//I won’t be able to sleep, that’s for sure. They’ll be loud all night, so, I might as well go.
I have to clean all the dead leaves off the telescope, and it’s so annoying.
I live at the observatory with my housemate, <NPCName>Chaem</>. Feel free to stop by any time!
You don’t know where it is?//It’s right behind the vineyard.//Do you know where the vineyard is?
Brrrr. My toes are going numb!
Seems like it’s been snowing for days…
This storm is intense! The wind must be blowing fifty miles an hour.
Stay safe, okay, <PlayerName>$player</>? I don’t want you to get hit by a flying object!
Gah! I <Italic>need</> to go to the Coffee Corner in front of Fishensips tomorrow.//<portrait=normal>The coffee is great, and nothing compares to their muffins!
I think <NpcName>Raj</> sources the coffee beans locally, but I’m not 100 percent sure.//If you’re curious, you should ask them. I don’t think they mind sharing that information!
One reason I think it’d be cool to travel is because the constellations look different in different places.//Isn’t that interesting?
I don’t eat much fish anymore, but salmon is still a favorite of mine.
Know what I could go for right now? A vegan taco.
Have you ever had cenil? So good! I’ve loved it since I was a kid.
I’m going to send you some cenil sometime. I hope that’s okay with you.//<portrait=happy>Don’t worry, it won’t be my cooking, so you can feast without fear! Heh heh!
Mangos are probably my favorite fruit. Just saying.
The cold is making me crave chocolate chip muffins.//Do you want some too?
I grew up on my dad’s fishing boat, the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. It was an unusual childhood, let me tell you!
I mean, it’s the only childhood I had, so it seemed normal to me.//<portrait=normal>But I was jealous of other kids who got to go to school and play sports… All those normal things.
That’s why it was really important to me to go to college.//<portrait=happy>To reclaim some of that normalcy. You know what I mean?
I tried to get in some stargazing last night, but it was too cloudy. Disappointing.//<portrait=normal>The Winter sky, huh?
Can’t talk right now. I have some numbers in my head, and I don’t want to lose them!//Gotta run to my computer and do some calculations…
<NPCName>Chaem</>? I’m not sure where she is. Why?//<portrait=annoyed>You should try the beach. She might be there practicing.
It’s really beautiful this time of year. Peaceful too.//<portrait=happy>Spring here is truly special.
Can you tell the difference between a star and a planet when you look at the night sky?//I guess it takes some practice.

For one thing, stars are like dots, but planets are more spherical. Stars cast their own light, like our sun, but planets reflect light. Also, stars twinkle. Planets don’t.//<portrait=happy>Sorry I got carried away talking about stars. I hope I didn’t bore you.
<PlayerName>$player</>! Are you going to the Cherry Blossom Festival?
I’ve been trying to get my dad to come, but he doesn’t want to.//<portrait=sad>Maybe you can help me convince him.
Sometimes I miss the Summer sunsets on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>. We had a panoramic view.
Summer days like these remind me of my childhood.//Dad and I used to spend nights looking at the stars on the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid</>.
Some of my most memorable Summers were spent at sea, I have to admit.
Growing up on a boat was tough. I didn’t have any friends my own age.//It might have stunted my social development.
Thanks, <PlayerName>$player</>. I always feel comfortable talking to you.
Ha ha, see? I say awkward things, and then the conversation just sort of…
Well… The more we know about each other, right?
One nice thing about being an astronomer is you can do it anywhere.
If I’d become a fisher like my dad wanted, I would have to be out at sea. But an astronomer has more freedom. There are stars wherever you go.
I’ve been thinking about where else I might live if my dad weren’t here.
Don’t tell him I said that, though.//<portrait=sad>I don’t want him to know I’ve been thinking about it. He’d take it wrong.
I learned how to play pool when I was young.//Some of the <Italic>Pithy Mermaid’s</> crew taught me when we were in port.
I guess they shouldn’t have been taking me into taverns at such a young age.//<portrait=normal>But no one ever stopped us!
There are so many dead leaves everywhere now. I hope they don’t get stuck in our drain.//That’d be a nightmare to clean.
The beach cleanup last week was a win, wasn’t it? A lot of people came to help.//<portrait=normal>It was really hot, but it was worth it. We did good!
I saw <NpcName>Takeba</> talking to some guy with scar on his face yesterday, mistaking him for his son again.//<portrait=sad>Poor man must really miss his son.
Does this hair color suit me, you think? I might dye it different color, if not.//But I have to leave it a couple weeks. Might have to wait till Winter.

<NpcName>Erika</> said my hair color is fitting for the “crispy season” now. I assumed she meant Fall…//<portrait=normal>I don’t really care about my hair fitting the season. Does it fit <Italic>my face</>?//Also, why is Fall “crispy”?
I like your Fall outfit.//It looks nice.
I had some pumpkin pie earlier today. The neighbor baked one too many and sent us some.//It was good, yeah… Nothing special, but yeah.

I walked past the cemetery last week, and it was mossy! Dead leaves everywhere. But then it was all nice and clean yesterday.//I think the Sanchez brothers are working extra hard cleaning it up this Fall. Good men.
Gloves are not for me. They feel weird on my hands… Hate the feel.//<portrait=annoyed>Not just that. They make my hands even colder. How is that possible?
Accidentally stepped in a puddle walking outside with no shoes on this morning.//<portrait=concerned>And now I can’t feel the toes on my right foot. Dang it!
Gah! I’ll be sure to always put on shoes from now on.
Enjoying the snow?

The observatory can get cold. For one, the building is huge, and it’s <Italic>really</> high.//The heater has to work <Italic>overtime</> to keep all that space warm.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s a waste of money to run the heat in the main area, so we usually only have it on in the bedrooms.
How do you keep moisturized in the dry Winter weather?//<portrait=annoyed>I’m drinking extra water, but it doesn’t seem to be enough. My hands feel like they’re made of ceramic that’s about to crack.
Sorry if that’s vivid. Maybe it isn’t the lack of humidity. Maybe it’s the dish soap. We got the cheapest one…//<portrait=annoyed>I’ll put gloves on when I do dishes. That’ll help, I’m sure.
If I’m right that bamboo shoots only grow during Spring, it means we have less than two weeks to gather them.
If I’m not mistaken, Dad once told me you can only get bamboo shoots in the bamboo forest.//Behind the observatory, right around the hot spring.
And bamboo shoots only grow during Spring! That makes them a rare find, doesn’t it?//<portrait=happy>All right, don’t quote me on the “only grow during Spring” bit. I’m not sure about that one.
[You wonder what song he’s humming. It’s upbeat.]//I love Spring days like this!
I should go to Sam’s and get some seeds for the lighthouse patch. We’re running out.
I’m thinking of buying radish seeds…or maybe strawberries. What’s better? They’re Spring seeds, aren’t they?//Which one do you think my Dad would like?
If I’m right, wasabi only grows during Spring, which means we have less than two weeks to gather it.
It’s all right. It’s a handy condiment for when you’re stargazing… Keeps you awake. Nothing special.

I’d camp out more often if it weren’t for the many massive mosquitos.//I do live in the middle of the forest, though. I can’t fault the mosquitos when I’m the one <Italic>trespassing</> in their home.
Not to mention it’s literally Summer right now. The season of bugs.
Is it corn season yet? Do you grow it on your farm?
The Beach Cleanup Festival is important to this community. It’s a good tradition.//I’m glad we’re keeping it alive.
The next one is going to be on the 27th.//<portrait=annoyed>Just come to the beach whenever you’re ready, and there should be a lot of people there setting up water booths and stuff.
Pulling up trash when you’re fishing isn’t a waste. That’s one less piece of trash in the water for fish to eat.//It makes a difference.
One of the good things about living at the observatory is that you can hear the bugs singing at night in Summer.
This wind is intense! If it were a bit stronger, I think it’d be a storm.
It’s snowing, isn’t it? You have snow on your nose.
Being out in the snow isn’t too bad.//It’s cold, but it’s not as cold as I thought it would be.
<NpcName>Chaem</> was going around covered in snow this morning. Boggles my mind why she doesn’t brush it off.//She likes it, I guess. Maybe it’s good for her training or something like that.
I’m nervous about seeing my dad this weekend.//I know he’s going to criticize me.
I don’t know what it’s going to be about, but I just <Italic>know</> he will.

Dad isn’t too happy about the moss on the lighthouse. He’s afraid it’s after his plants, he said.//No matter how hard we try to get rid of it, the moss comes back. It’s <Italic>moss</>, for crying out loud!
I think even with all the moss, the lighthouse is in great shape… It’s an old building. But it doesn’t matter.//<Italic>Nothing</> will ever be good enough for him.

Living in an inn like <NpcName>Raj</> sounds good, in a way. Especially when there’s a lot of snow storms like this.//They said the heater runs okay most of the time, and even when it doesn’t, the twins make sure all the guests have extra blankets.
They said it’s worth every penny!
Talked to <NpcName>Aaliyah</> one time. That girl is probably one of the smartest people I’ve ever met.//<portrait=normal>It must take a lot of work to be that knowledgeable and accomplished.
Sometimes I wish I had Dad’s skills. The green thumb, the fishing instinct, whatever.//<portrait=sad>He’s so good with nature. I’m nowhere close to that.
You’re a good person, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad you moved here.
